Answer: You can use a join for this:

\begin{code}
SELECT s.Name, Count(s.ID) AS Count
FROM stadium s
LEFT JOIN singer_in_concert si
    ON si.Stadium_ID = s.ID AND si.Singer_ID IS NOT NULL
WHERE si.Singer_ID IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY s.Name
ORDER BY Count DESC, s.Name ASC;
\end{code}

